Reasoning: The paper discusses scheduling applications on distributed computing resources, specifically cloud, edge, and fog computing. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper focuses on the Internet of Things (IoT) deployments, which is a subfield of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses application programming and scheduling models, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses Quality of Service (QoS) constraints and goals, which is a subfield of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the design and categorization of applications, which falls under the category of Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
